gy cascade leads to an\nasymptotic density slope $\\gamma=-4/3$ for fully virialized haloes with a\nvanishing radial flow, which might explain the nearly universal halo density.\nBased on the continuity equation, halo density is analytically shown to be\nclosely dependent on the radial flow and mass accretion, such that simulated\nhaloes can have different limiting slopes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 7 Sep 2022 17:18:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 14 Mar 2023 00:08:53 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 27 May 2023 07:10:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-30"}
