ving the ecliptic plane, which is rich in young stellar associations,\nso we anticipate many more discoveries in the TESS dataset. A larger sample of\ndipper stars would enhance the census statistics of light curve morphologies\nand dipper ages.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 7 Sep 2022 18:00:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-16"}
