rised by a distinct velocity as seen from the emission peak of\nCH$_{3}$OH lines. They also show transonic and supersonic motions. SiO is\nassociated with filaments and also with multiple bow-shock features. In\naddition, for the first time, we reveal a highly collimated SiO jet\n(~1$^{\\circ}$) with a projected length of ~5200 au from the embedded protostar\nVLA15. Our study shows that multi-scale observations of these regions are\ncrucial for understanding the accretion processes and flow of material that\nshapes star formation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 8 Sep 2022 10:31:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-02"}
